Subject: [ghostium] Navigator hardwareConcurrency hook

Spec-E wiring. Anchors at top of ``navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc``.
The real call into ``FingerprintNoiseSource::HardwareConcurrencyOverride``
lands inside ``NavigatorConcurrentHardware::hardwareConcurrency`` and
fires only when no upstream emulation override is active.

The companion ``deviceMemory`` surface lives in ``navigator.cc`` and
is anchored by patch 0002 to avoid colliding on the same top-of-file
line range.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc
@@ -1,3 +1,9 @@
 // Copyright 2014 The Chromium Authors
 // Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
 // found in the LICENSE file.
+// GHOSTIUM-HOOK-ANCHOR: Spec-E hardwareConcurrency surface.
+//   NavigatorConcurrentHardware::hardwareConcurrency consults
+//   FingerprintNoiseSource::HardwareConcurrencyOverride; deviceMemory
+//   is anchored by patch 0002 in navigator.cc. See
+//   //ghostium_src/overlay/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/ghostium_fp/fingerprint_noise_source.h
+//   and plan.md section 4.7.
